"use strict";(self.webpackChunkdocumentation=self.webpackChunkdocumentation||[]).push([[5098],{2492:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"new-ui","metadata":{"permalink":"/stale/blog/new-ui","editUrl":"https://github.com/Sonia-corporation/stale/tree/develop/documentation/blog/2022-02-12-new-ui/index.mdx","source":"@site/blog/2022-02-12-new-ui/index.mdx","title":"The new UI is here!","description":"The UI of this action changed from blue to pink.\\nThe name was also updated to reflect that this action belongs to the Sonia corporation collective group of open-source projects.\\n","date":"2022-02-12T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"February 12, 2022","tags":[{"label":"new ui","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/new-ui"},{"label":"pink","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/pink"},{"label":"brand","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/brand"},{"label":"sonia","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/sonia"},{"label":"sonia corporation","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/sonia-corporation"}],"readingTime":0.555,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Geoffrey \\"C0ZEN\\" Testelin","title":"Creator and maintainer of this Sonia stale action","url":"https://github.com/C0ZEN","imageURL":"https://github.com/C0ZEN.png","key":"C0ZEN"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"new-ui","title":"The new UI is here!","description":"The UI of this action changed from blue to pink.\\nThe name was also updated to reflect that this action belongs to the Sonia corporation collective group of open-source projects.\\n","authors":["C0ZEN"],"tags":["new ui","pink","brand","sonia","sonia corporation"],"hide_table_of_contents":false},"nextItem":{"title":"The first inclusive filter input is here!","permalink":"/stale/blog/first-inclusive-input"}},"content":"The brand-new UI of the stale action is here, changing the name and the colour palette!\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Re-branding {#re-branding}\\n\\nIn order to keep consistency with the other projects inside the [Sonia corporation organization](https://github.com/Sonia-corporation?type=source), the action name was changed in some places to reflect that it\'s a \\"Sonia thing\\".  \\nThe logo was changed from a thermostat to just the usual Sonia logo.\\n\\n## Colour palette {#colour-palette}\\n\\nThe previous colour palette was a cold blue, to reflect the \\"stale\\" state of the items.  \\nNow, everything is pink, to follow the dress colour inside the Sonia\'s logo.\\n\\n**Before:**\\n\\n![Example banner](../../static/img/before-rebranding-to-sonia.png)\\n\\n**After:**\\n\\n![Example banner](../../static/img/after-rebranding-to-sonia.png)\\n\\nWe hope you like, and if not, blame Sonia. :wink:"},{"id":"first-inclusive-input","metadata":{"permalink":"/stale/blog/first-inclusive-input","editUrl":"https://github.com/Sonia-corporation/stale/tree/develop/documentation/blog/2022-02-11-first-inclusive-input/index.mdx","source":"@site/blog/2022-02-11-first-inclusive-input/index.mdx","title":"The first inclusive filter input is here!","description":"This stale action now contains the first input of the genre: an inclusive filter!\\nThis will change how the ignoring process can be leverage to process only items that matters!\\n","date":"2022-02-11T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"February 11, 2022","tags":[{"label":"input","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/input"},{"label":"new kind","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/new-kind"},{"label":"ignoring process","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/ignoring-process"},{"label":"projects","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/projects"},{"label":"inclusive criteria","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/inclusive-criteria"}],"readingTime":1.195,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Geoffrey \\"C0ZEN\\" Testelin","title":"Creator and maintainer of this Sonia stale action","url":"https://github.com/C0ZEN","imageURL":"https://github.com/C0ZEN.png","key":"C0ZEN"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"first-inclusive-input","title":"The first inclusive filter input is here!","description":"This stale action now contains the first input of the genre: an inclusive filter!\\nThis will change how the ignoring process can be leverage to process only items that matters!\\n","authors":["C0ZEN"],"tags":["input","new kind","ignoring process","projects","inclusive criteria"],"hide_table_of_contents":false},"prevItem":{"title":"The new UI is here!","permalink":"/stale/blog/new-ui"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome!","permalink":"/stale/blog/welcome"}},"content":"The first input of the inclusive filtering kind is out!\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## TL;DR {#tldr}\\n\\nThe input [issue-only-any-project-cards](../docs/issues/inputs/issue-only-any-project-cards-input) is out!  \\nYou can now only process your issues when they are linked to a project.\\n\\n## A bit of context {#a-bit-of-context}\\n\\nAll the inputs added so far were useful to ignore all the items not having certain criteria.\\n\\nFor example, the only inputs available to ignore the processing of issues for a project were the [issue-ignore-all-project-cards](../docs/issues/inputs/issue-ignore-all-project-cards-input) and the [issue-ignore-any-project-cards](../docs/issues/inputs/issue-ignore-any-project-cards-input) inputs.  \\nBut what if you only wish to process issues that belongs to a specific project?  \\nYou simply couldn\'t!\\n\\nHaving inputs to reverse the logic to only process by using inclusive criteria was not something possible so far.\\n\\n## What is new? {#what-is-new}\\n\\nTo tackle this issue and be able to only process issues that belongs to a specific project or to a specific list of projects, we needed a new input.  \\nSo, the input [issue-only-any-project-cards](../docs/issues/inputs/issue-only-any-project-cards-input) was created for this purpose.\\n\\n## Why is that so important? {#why-is-that-so-important}\\n\\nDeveloping those features are not that hard, but thinking about how to combine them all together in a way that makes sense is a bit more difficult.  \\nBut now we have a recipe to _inclusive inputs_, and we will be able to provide more functionalities following the same scheme! :rocket:\\n\\n:::info\\n\\nYou can see an [advanced example](../docs/examples/multiple-cron-example) to configure different workflows with multiple cron that may help you fine-tune even more the action.\\n\\n:::"},{"id":"welcome","metadata":{"permalink":"/stale/blog/welcome","editUrl":"https://github.com/Sonia-corporation/stale/tree/develop/documentation/blog/2022-01-20-first-website-draft/index.mdx","source":"@site/blog/2022-01-20-first-website-draft/index.mdx","title":"Welcome!","description":"Welcome to the very first version of the Website!\\n","date":"2022-01-20T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 20, 2022","tags":[{"label":"stale","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/stale"},{"label":"website","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/website"},{"label":"documentation","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/documentation"},{"label":"first draft","permalink":"/stale/blog/tags/first-draft"}],"readingTime":0.575,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Geoffrey \\"C0ZEN\\" Testelin","title":"Creator and maintainer of this Sonia stale action","url":"https://github.com/C0ZEN","imageURL":"https://github.com/C0ZEN.png","key":"C0ZEN"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome","title":"Welcome!","description":"Welcome to the very first version of the Website!\\n","authors":["C0ZEN"],"tags":["stale","website","documentation","first draft"],"hide_table_of_contents":false},"prevItem":{"title":"The first inclusive filter input is here!","permalink":"/stale/blog/first-inclusive-input"}},"content":"Happy to announce that this is the very first version of this website!\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Why even bother? {#why-even-bother}\\n\\nWe really think that handling a huge number of issues on a repository is time-consuming, a real grunt task in a way.  \\nWe hope that by adding this website, you will have access to even further help to let you customize your stale action at your convenience.  \\nThe configuration can be complex when you have strong requirements, but it\'s OK!\\n\\n## Share your work! {#share-your-work}\\n\\nBy letting the community know your configuration, it can help to clarify what kind of scenarios to expect from this action.  \\nDo not hesitate to [open a new blog article suggestion](https://github.com/Sonia-corporation/stale/issues/new/choose)."}]}')}}]);